ooh bard fixes, i fucking cringe every time i see a godamn bard &quot;fix&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
To educate some of the non bards, the first bug has been with bads for 3 years.   On rare occasions with alot of lag, bards would experience a *song lockup*<br>
<br>
this lockup would basically make one song play over and over, and there was no way to stop it, and impossible to start another song.   To fix it you had to zone/camp  or spamm the shit out of your songs for like 20 sec smashing your song hotkey, and it might or might not break the lock.<br>
<br>
It was an annoying bug that they had trouble reproducing, but it was rare as hell, and we lived with it.<br>
<br>
<br>
The second *fix*  Did an even greater lockup than the said above one, your spell gems became disabled period upon procing with a buff that allowed you to do so (Katta's Boon of the Garou)   I honestly have no idea how long this has been around, since Ive never seen the need for boon of garou buff, or the new tricksters.<br>
<br>
It became prety prevalent when bards started using Katta's sworddancing, since the proc it gave you was semi usefull on rampaging and flurry type mobs, a -25 dex debuff.<br>
<br>
<br>
Same as above, a very annoying bug, that I would have loved to see gone, but also livable.  If  no shaman or enc was around to cripple i would play the song, cease to attack and have the group inform me upon procing.<br>
<br>
<br>
They claimed to have *fixed* these too bugs.  Well what they claimed and what happened are not even fucking close.<br>
<br>
<br>
This is what the so called *fix* did.<br>
<br>
If we are singing somthing(always are) and we proc a weapon(like our epic that is surgially bonded to our off hand)  Our songs lock as in the first said bug.<br>
<br>
We can fix this 3 ways.  Zone/camp(ha!)  smash our song hotkeys till it rights itself, or use a right click non instacast item, duck out of it, then resume singing.  It seems rather harmless at first glance true.  In practice its a fucking fiasco.   During combat our entire exsistance is in a constant state of casting.   A lvl 60 bard doing their job right  is always in the process of juggling 3-5 effects with durations ranging mostly from 12 sec to up to 2.5 min.   It takes perfect timing precision, and cadence to keep this stuff going.   Every time we proc we have to drop the entire weave we are doing, all our effects, and rythm lost, to fix this fucking bug.<br>
<br>
In general it makes it so we can realistically do two things:<br>
<br>
1) play one song, and melee<br>
2) no more melee and do our normal jobs.<br>
<br>
<br>
This is beyond unacceptable, its really along the lines of telling a rogue they can either melee or backstab but not both, or a cleric you can heal or buff, but not both.<br>
<br>
